<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-11254] Promoting AccessControlList to be public</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-11254</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The motivation of promoting AccessControlList to be a public API is to facilitate the users to programmatically parse or construct an ACL string. A typical use case may be the timeline domain, where we have the client lib to accept strings complied with ACL string format to define the authorized readers/writers. It will be more convenient and less buggy if users can compose this string with AccessControlList.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12752023">HADOOP-11254</key>
